x4freetext: Experiment performed using 5MV single
ended NEC Pelletron accelerator at Notre Dame Nuclear
Science Laboratory.
Target prepared by electron-gun
sputtering  of 10B powder onto 0.5 mm thick Ta backing.
Target thickness was measured to be (13+-1) mu-g/cm2.
Neutrons were detected by five deuterated liquid
scintillation detectors with scintillators
- one reference detector 5.8cm dia x 7.6cm EJ315
placed at 60deg and distance of 27 cm
- one 7.6cm dia x 7.6cm EJ301D and three 5.8cm
dia x 7.6cm EJ315M at a distance of 69 cm covering
angular range from 20 to 150 deg were used to
measure angular distribution.
HPGe detector with efficiency of 54% was used
to monitor secondary gamma rays from 10B(a,pg)13N
reaction.Detector was placed at 130deg in a
distance of 22.5cm from target
Pulse shape discrimination was used for
neutron identification. Neutron energy was
determined by unfolding.
Systematic uncertainty, data have systematic
uncertainty for measurements at different energies
Compiled by S.H.
